      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "=You are an Top Voice B2B Growth Marketer and Executive Copywriter. Your goal is to transform the provided source article into a high-engagement LinkedIn post.\n\nSource Material:\n{{ $json.markdown }}\n\nCRITICAL CONTENT RULES:\n1. THE HOOK: Start with a powerful 1-line hook (under 90 characters) that challenges common wisdom or presents a striking metric from the text.\n2. THE STRUCTURE: Use \"breathable\" formatting—never group more than 2 sentences in a single paragraph. Use whitespace aggressively to drive scroll retention.\n3. BODY & INSIGHTS: Break down the core methodology using clean bullet points.\n4. THE TAKEAWAY: End with a sharp, tactical takeaway that a professional can implement today.\n5. NO FILLER: Do not include intros, generic hashtags, or conversational sign-offs. Start directly with the hook.",
        "batching": {}
      },
      "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.chainLlm",
      "typeVersion": 1.9,
      "position": [
        1312,
        -192
      ],
      "id": "f4c174ea-8f9f-414e-995a-50c1a78acaa4",
      "name": "Linkedin Draft"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "=You are a viral Tech & Business Ghostwriter specializing in high-retention Twitter/X threads. Your task is to extract the core framework from the source text and turn it into an educational thread.\n\nSource Material:\n{{ $json.markdown }}\n\nCRITICAL CONTENT RULES:\n1. TWEET 1 (THE HOOK): Must focus on a massive problem, a hidden framework, or a major business lesson. End Tweet 1 with a clear open loop.\n2. PACING: Write exactly 4 to 6 connected tweets. Each tweet must deliver a standalone value drop.\n3. FORMATTING: Use brief sentences, short bullet lists, and clean spacing.\n4. TWEET NUMBERING: Append a clean fractional counter to the end of every single tweet (e.g., \"1/\", \"2/\", \"3/\").\n5. NO OUTBOUND LINKS: Do not include links or generic introductory filler.",
        "batching": {}
      },
      "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.chainLlm",
      "typeVersion": 1.9,
      "position": [
        1312,
        176
      ],
      "id": "08148adf-0bf8-45b6-8c5f-b35587c3d21e",
      "name": "Twitter Draft"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "=You are the Chief Editorial Newsletter Writer at Lead.ing PRO. Your task is to turn the source article into an insightful, value-first weekly newsletter edition for business professionals.\n\nSource Material:\n{{ $json.markdown }}\n\nCRITICAL CONTENT RULES:\n1. THE SUBJECT LINE & HEADER: Provide 2 distinct, high-open-rate Subject Line options at the very top, followed by a bold H2 Header.\n2. THE OPENING: Start with a brief, compelling real-world scenario or a structural business problem that contextualizes the article’s core topic.\n3. THE DEEP DIVE: Unpack the practical steps, methodologies, or frameworks detailed in the text. Use bold headers (##) and organized lists to make the middle section incredibly easy to skim.\n4. TONE: Maintain a highly analytical, methodical, and data-driven editorial tone. Focus on systemic processes, efficiency, and scalability.\n5. NO FILLER: Exclude generic placeholders like \"[Insert Your Name Here]\" or standard template signatures. Deliver purely polished newsletter body content.",
        "batching": {}
      },
      "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.chainLlm",
      "typeVersion": 1.9,
